  "local_port": 41082,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some things new employees should know going into their first day at Universal?",
  "response": "Starting a new job at Universal can be an exciting experience. Here's a list of things that might be helpful to know for your first day:\n\n1. **Company Overview**: Familiarize yourself with Universal's history, core values, and mission. Understanding the company culture will help you integrate smoothly.\n\n2. **Dress Code**: Make sure to check the dress code policy beforehand. Some roles may have specific uniforms or attire guidelines.\n\n3. **Location and Commute**: Plan your commute in advance to ensure you arrive on time. If possible, do a test run a day before to gauge traffic and timing.\n\n4. **Orientation Schedule**: You might have an orientation session on your first day. This could include meeting your team, understanding your role, and getting an overview of company operations.\n\n5. **Human Resources Paperwork**: Be prepared to complete necessary HR paperwork, such as tax forms and direct deposit details. Bring any required identification documents.\n\n6. **Technology Setup**: You may need to set up your computer, email, and other necessary software tools. If possible, gather information on the IT support available.\n\n7. **Workplace Policies**: Take some time to read through the employee handbook to understand workplace policies, including those related to vacation, sick leave, and conduct.\n\n8. **Networking**: Introduce yourself to colleagues and try to remember names. Building a good rapport early on can make a big difference.\n\n9. **Lunch Options**: Check out nearby dining options or inquire if there\u2019s an on-site cafeteria. Your orientation might also include details about lunch breaks.\n\n10. **Ask Questions**: Don\u2019t hesitate to ask questions if you\u2019re unsure about anything. It\u2019s better to clarify doubts early on.\n\n11. **Key Contacts**: Identify who your key contacts are, such as your manager, HR representative, and any teammates you'll be working closely with.\n\n12. **Company Perks**: Learn about any employee benefits or perks offered by Universal, such as discounts, health benefits, or wellness programs.\n\n13. **First Impressions**: Arrive on time, be enthusiastic, and show a willingness to learn. Your attitude can make a significant impact on first impressions.\n\nBy preparing in advance and tackling your first day with confidence, you'll be setting a solid foundation for your career at Universal.",
